main event: A radar object was detected near Seffner, Florida that was described as a 'golf ball traveling east to west and changing colors'.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar for 20 minutes.
The object was described as being the size of a golf ball.
The object changed colors from red to green to orange.
The object faded away after 20 minutes of observation.
The report concluded there was 'insufficient data for analysis' due to contradictory statements by the observer.
sighted object: a radar target described as a 'golf ball' changing colors
